<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="510" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.248/55⅓</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of
                                        State</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief
                                        of the Division of Near Eastern Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Murray</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-06">December 6,
                                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Murray</hi>: I wish you would talk with
                                    Dr. Berle and Mr. Philip Young regarding the matter dealt with
                                    in the attached letter<note n="84" xml:id="d510fn84">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                                    </note> from the Greek Minister. It is the President’s most
                                    positive desire that these thirty planes be released to the
                                    Greek Government. Surely some satisfactory way can be found of
                                    doing it.</p>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>